article.headline: New Hampshire 62, MD Baltimore Co 60
article.story: CATONSVILLE, Md. (AP) -- Ben Sturgill scored off Blagoj Janev's missed 3-pointer with .4 seconds remaining in regulation, lifting New Hampshire over the University of Maryland, Baltimore County 62-60 Wednesday night. Sturgill scored 20 points as the Wildcats (7-18, 3-12 America East) snapped a two-game losing streak. Janev and Craig Walls each had 12 points for New Hampshire. Rob Gogerty led UMBC (7-17, 4-11) with 19 points and Kareem Washington had 16. The Retrievers have dropped three straight and seven of eight. Sturgill outleaped two defenders after a left-side miss by Janev for the decisive basket before floating a two-handed shot into the net while in midair. Cory McJimson's spinning layup through traffic gave UMBC a 60-58 lead with 1:31 left in the game, but New Hampshire tied the game on a pair of Janev free throws with 1:12 to go. The Wildcats' Griffin Walker was called for traveling with 38.1 seconds remaining, but Jermaine Anderson blocked Washington's 3-point attempt from the right corner with 15 seconds left, setting the stage for Sturgill's dramatic put-back. Sturgill scored the first eight points of the second half for the Wildcats, who trailed 24-16 at halftime after hitting only 5-of-25 shots from the field in the first half. But a 16-for-21 second half from the field rallied New Hampshire. The Retrievers wiped away an early 6-2 deficit with a 16-4 run. Washington had nine points during the burst, starting it with a baseline jumper and finishing it with a press-breaking layup and a 3-pointer from the right side.
